title: `$anemon::alter()`
description: This is just a shortcut for `switch` and `case` statements.
...

~~~ .php.xmp
Anemon::alter($input, $replace = [], $fail = null);
~~~

**Example:**

~~~ .php
$input = 'bar';

$test = Anemon::alter($input, [
    'foo' => 1,
    'bar' => 2,
    'baz' => 3
]);
~~~

Result:

~~~ .php
$test = 2;
~~~